HEADWORD: Tridymite
<hw>Trid"y*mite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
threefold. So called in allusion to the supposed threefold nature of the
twin crystals.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Pure silica, like quartz,
but crystallizing in hexagonal tables. It is found in trachyte and
similar rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tried</ent>⟦br⟧
